## Executive Summary

This document represents the definitive, rulebook-integrated blueprint for Off-World Basketball, synthesizing all prior research iterations (Versions 1.0–4.0) with formal SGF-style competition rules. The sport is codified as a Bullet-Time discipline within the "same-stadium" physics framework validated by Fraundorf (2025) and supported by findings from academic biomechanics research, commercial space habitat developments, and space-sports governance initiatives.

This document establishes Off-World Basketball as:

- A competitive sport governed by the Space Games Federation® (SGF), with players designated as Astroletes®
- A physiological countermeasure against hypogravity deconditioning, integrating NASA Human Research Program findings including LBNP (Lower Body Negative Pressure) protocols
- A flagship entertainment product for off-world habitats, positioned within a rapidly emerging global space sports industry
- A complete rulebook (v1.0) ready for SGF certification and EqualSpace™ Challenge submission

