## PART VI: APPENDICES

### Appendix A: Definitions

| Term | Definition |
|---|---|
| Astrolete® | SGF-certified athlete trained for hypogravity competition. Term combines "astronaut" and "athlete." |
| Bullet-Time | Gameplay state where extended hang time allows multi-player aerial tactics and slow-motion decision-making |
| Orbital Loitering | Air Timer violation; exceeding maximum legal hang time without releasing ball |
| Launch Reset | Illegal use of surface contact to extend flight time without releasing ball |
| Landing Zone Foul | Defender occupying opponent's projected landing ellipse within 1.0 second of predicted touchdown |
| Orbital Set | Offensive strategy involving multiple Astroletes® airborne simultaneously, passing in slow arcs |
| Apex Cannon Insertion | Method of initiating play; ball launched to mid-court apex by compressed-air cannon |
| Same-Stadium Approach | Modified ball in off-world stadium; produces slower "bullet-time" gameplay with enhanced momentum effects |
| Same-Ball Approach | Earth ball in off-world stadium; produces more energetic, faster gameplay |
| Bullet-Time Official (BTO) | Referee responsible for Air Timer monitoring, Landing Zone Foul detection, and IMU data review |
| High-μ Grid | SGF-certified flooring with enhanced coefficient of friction to normalize stopping distance in hypogravity |
| Wall of Death | Banked perimeter section of court (30–45°) enabling horizontal running via centripetal force; serves as training countermeasure and gameplay feature |
| LBNP | Lower Body Negative Pressure; NASA-developed technology simulating gravitational loading on lower extremities |
| IMU | Inertial Measurement Unit; embedded ball sensor logging spin, release vector, and possession timer |
| CoR (e) | Coefficient of Restitution; ratio of post-impact to pre-impact velocity; measures bounce |
| SGF | Space Games Federation®; governing and sanctioning body for competitive sports in hypogravity |

